# Inventory Decision Engine Architecture

The Inventory Decision Engine is designed to automate inventory-related decisions across buying, replenishment, allocation and pricing.

The system architecture is organised into five layers:

1. Data Sources
2. Data Processing
3. Decision Engines
4. Execution Systems
5. Monitoring & Learning


                 +----------------------+
                 |      Data Sources     |
                 | Sales, Inventory,     |
                 | Vendor, Product Data  |
                 +----------+-----------+
                            |
                            v
                 +----------------------+
                 |  Data Processing     |
                 | Feature Engineering  |
                 | SKU Segmentation     |
                 | Forecast Integration |
                 +----------+-----------+
                            |
                            v
               +----------------------------+
               |     Decision Engines        |
               | Smart Buying                |
               | Replenishment Engine        |
               | Store Allocation Engine     |
               | Inventory Placement Engine  |
               | Ageing Detection Engine     |
               | Pricing Optimisation        |
               +-------------+---------------+
                             |
                             v
                 +----------------------------+
                 |   Execution Systems        |
                 | ERP (Purchase Order)       |
                 | PO SPLIT                   |
                 | ARS (Replenishment)        |
                 | WMS (Warehouse Inv)        |
                 | Allocation & Consolidation |
                 +-----------+----------------+
                             |
                             v
                 +-----------------------+
